tweets.text: Points are the most valuable asset in the @virtuals_io ecosystem. Be aggressive spending points where you can get value, but cautious on hyped launches where points are heavily diluted. Your $ returns per point spent are more important than $ returns per $VIRTUAL spent. While you can get 100x - 1000x in terms of $VIRTUAL spent on hyped launches, most users are making very little in terms of raw dollars because they can only allocate a few $VIRTUAL tokens on the most hyped launches. For example, $IRIS gave $0.010 per a point spent. Not great, not terrible. Sure, it was a safer play because you were guaranteed to get huge returns per $VIRTUAL spent, but you also received only $0.010 per a point spent. Twelve launches gave better $ returns per a point spent, including even the recent $DUCK @appduckai.

tweets.text: There's so much noise in the info-fi space atm it's hard to know which projects to focus us. On top of that KAITO rewards creators for loyalty, meaning you ultimately get nerfed somewhat for trying to climb too many leaderboards. Focus on products that you actually use & have invested capital in. For me that means putting 99% of my content towards: @virtuals_io @katana @infinex @multibank_io Nobody wants to see the same updates about reward programs and where you are on the leaderboard in every post. We want to see what you are actually doing with those products. - How much money are you making? - What is your strategy? - How much capital are you risking? Such things actually help others make decisions and hopefully win together.
